              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".The collective-excitation mechanism and the",
                "coupled-channel method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The angular dependences of the differential",
                "cross sections were measured in an individual",
                "experiment by a semiconductor surface-barrier detector",
                "arranged beyond the scattering chamber. In that case,",
                "scattered alpha particles escaped from the scattering",
                "chamber through a horizontal slit covered with a thin",
                " 20 mum Mylar window. In measuring double-differential",
                "cross sections, four silicon semiconductor surface-",
                "barrier detectors (SBD) with a sensitive area up to",
                "400 mum in thickness were used. The detectors were",
                "arranged with in the scattering chamber 230 mm in",
                "diameter on a table whose angle of inclination with",
                "respect to a horizontal plane could be changed."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ". Gamma rays were detected by four scintillation",
                "detectors BDEG-23 based on NaI(Tl) crystals 63 mm in",
                "height and diameter"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
